BEGIN_PGML
To estimate the health of the Rocky Mountain elk population in the Wenaha Wildlife Area, the Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife caught, tagged, and released [`[$tt]`] Rocky Mountain elk. A month later, they returned and observed [`[$sp]`] Rocky Mountain elk, [`[$st]`] of which had tags. Approximately how many Rocky Mountain elk are in the Wenaha Wildlife Area?

[_]{$ans}{16}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Let [`x`] represent how many elk are in the Wenaha Wildlife Area. We set up a proportional equation:

[```\newcommand{\multiplyright}[2][\cdot]{{\highlight{{{}#1#2}}}}\newcommand{\divideunder}[2]{\frac{#1}{{\highlight{{#2}}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\frac{\text{tagged elk}}{\text{total elk}} \amp= \frac{\text{tagged elk}}{\text{total elk}}\\
\frac{[$st]}{[$sp]} \amp= \frac{[$tt]}{x}\\
\frac{[$st]}{[$sp]} \multiplyright{[$sp]\cdot x} \amp= \frac{[$tt]}{x}\multiplyright{[$sp]\cdot x}\\
[$st] \cdot x \amp= [$tt]\cdot [$sp]\\
\divideunder{[$st] \cdot x}{[$st]} \amp= \divideunder{[$tt]\cdot [$sp]}{[$st]}\\
x \amp= [$ans]
\end{aligned}
```]

There are approximately [`[$ans]`] elk in the Wenaha Wildlife Area.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

